data.name: EditBuildIntroduction
data.value: The Artifact Optimizer uses Builds to determine the efficiency of artifacts. This tutorial should give you the information you need to understand and manipulate them to fit your personal preferences. To edit a build, navigate to Builds and click on the build you want to edit.

data.name: OptimizerImgFourDesc
data.value:
The last artifact in the list has MAX. That means that if you get here you should change your ingame step amount to maximum and put the rest of your relics into this artifact.
If you get the message "Not enough relics" then this can mean two things: 1. You have to earn more relics. Play the game, prestige and reload the optimizer 2. Your BoS% is lower than the value in the settings. Put relics into Book of Shadows or reduce the amount in the settings

data.name: OptimizerImgOneDesc
data.value: Before you start to work with the optimizer keep sure to have your settings right. To enter them click on the pen which is highlighted in the picture.

data.name: OptimizerImgThreeDesc
data.value:
When the optimizer has done it's work you get a list of Artifacts to upgrade. Go from the top to the bottom. You see a picture and the name of the artifact to level. Beneath the Name you see the current level and in the brackets you see how much of your lifetime spent relics has gone into this artifact.
Next to that you see a box which tells you how often you should press the button the level this artifact. Here it says 12x (meaning press 12 times on the upgrade button of that artifact).

data.name: OptimizerImgTwoDesc
data.value:
Here you see the settings you can make. On the left of each setting you will find an info-button. Click on it to get a short description of what you can set.
First select a build which fits your playstile. You can use a predefined build (_ as first letter) or one of your own ones.
After that, set your pushing type. If you want to take advantage from silent march but mainly play online set this to "Not Set".
Next there is the step amount. Here you set the same value that you use ingame! The lower the step amount the more precise the optimization. But it should not be too low. The optimal value is 5%.
BoS Royalty is the percentual amount of relics you want to put into Book of Shadows outside of a Tournament. Most player push BoS outside of tournaments and inside of tournaments they ignore it.
BoS T-Royalty is the same inside of tournaments. This value should not be higher than outside of a tournament. Most players set this value to 0, which means that Book of Shadows will be totally ignored while you are in a tournament.
Hero: Is the damage type spell, melee or ranged? This setting is used to ignore artifacts. If you set melee you do not need to increase an artifact which strenghens ranged heroes
Range: Same as above
Gold Source: Set the gold source. Where do you get your gold from?

data.name: OptimizerIntroduction
data.value: This tutorial is meant to help you understanding the Artifact optimizer. The advantage you get using this optimizer is that you do not have to keep track of any value. You set this up once and are good to run. With the correct usage you can save a lot of time. One last thing before we start: When you level your artifacts it is suggested that you use the splitscreen-function of your phone. On the top you have Tap Titans open and on the button you have the optimizer. So now let's get started. First we will dive into the settings. After that we take a look at the list which is produced by the optimizer.

data.value: If you click on the Info-Button left to the entries you will get a description on what the fields mean.

data.name: SPFollowerIntroduction
data.value: With the SP Follower you can compare your skill tree with others and follow them. Some builds are seperated into multiple milestones which makes the tracking easier. On the skills tab - colors are indicating differences and if you can afford to level up a skill. Green: You have enough Skill Points to level up Orange: You should level this but have not enough Skill Points Red: The level of this skill is too high Neutral: The level is just fine

data.name: StatisticsImgOneDesc
data.value: From the statistics main menu you can create new snapshots. For supporter there is auto-snapshotting which creates a snapshot each time you open the app (and keeps one per day). With the button above you can manually create a new snapshot. Below you will find a list of your stored snapshots which you can enter by clicking on it.

data.name: StatisticsImgThreeDesc
data.value: If you enter a clan member you can see some information which is collected from your stored snapshots. You see how many stages, TP and clan quests the player increased

data.name: StatisticsImgTwoDesc
data.value:
This is the detailed view of a Snapshot. for each member in your clan you see some information like the name or the maximum stage. Here is a list of what the fields mean: CQ-T: The total clan quests CQ-W: Clan quests this week Tourn.: The amount of Tournaments the player has joined TP: The total amount of TP the player earned.
By clicking the bin you delete the snapshot and by clicking on the arrow you will export the snapshot to a csv-file.

data.name: StatisticsIntroduction
data.value: The statistics module is meant to provide you some information about the progress of you and you clan mates and are seperated into "Snapshots". Each snapshot holds relevant informations which you can export or view in the app. To prevent a too high collection of Snapshots you can set the maximum amount that should be stored in the Settings menu.

Az alkalmazás mindig naplózza az alapvető információkat. Ez az információ azonban soha nem kerül automatikusan elküldésre.
Ha kritikus hiba történik az alkalmazáson belül, lehetősége van e-mailt küldeni a fejlesztőnek. Ha ez megtörtént, az alkalmazás megpróbálja csatolni a naplófájlokat.
Bizonyos esetekben szükséges, hogy a fejlesztő részletes naplót kapjon. Ennek létrehozásához kérjük, a következőképpen járjon el: Lépjen a beállításokra, és aktiválja a részletes naplózást. Ezután próbálja meg újra létrehozni a problémát a lehető legkevesebb lépésben. Ezután lépjen vissza a beállításokhoz, és kapcsolja ki a részletes naplózást. Most lépjen a "Beszólás" oldalra, és kattintson a "Mail küldése" gombra.
